//! H.264 CAVLC residual entropy coding (coeff_token, levels, total_zeros, run_before).
//!
//! This is the entropy coder for the COMPRESSED-intra path — it replaces I_PCM's
//! raw bytes with real VLC-coded residuals, yielding far smaller files.
//!
//! Pure Rust, `std`+`alloc` only. No external crates, no threads. wasm32-safe.
//!
//! Implements ITU-T H.264 §9.2 `residual_block_cavlc`. The VLC tables embedded
//! below are transcribed from the H.264 / ISO-IEC 14496-10 spec:
//!   * Table 9-5  — coeff_token mapping (the four luma nC ranges + nC == -1
//!     chroma-DC range; nC == -2 / 4:2:2 chroma-DC is NOT implemented, see note).
//!   * Table 9-7 / 9-8 — total_zeros tables for 4×4 blocks (maxNumCoeff == 16),
//!     indexed by TotalCoeff (1..=15).
//!   * Table 9-9(a) — total_zeros tables for chroma-DC 2×2 (maxNumCoeff == 4).
//!   * Table 9-10 — run_before tables, indexed by zerosLeft (1..=6, with 6
//!     covering "6 or greater").
//!
//! NOTE on input ordering: `coeffs` MUST be supplied in ZIG-ZAG scan order (the
//! order produced by reordering a raster 4×4 block through
//! `crate::h264_transform::ZIGZAG4`). The first element is the DC / lowest
//! frequency, the last element the highest frequency. CAVLC scans from the
//! highest-frequency coefficient downward.

use crate::h264_bitstream::BitWriter;

